  "texts": [
    "One of the boundaries of H is the circle ∂.",
    "Let ∂ ′ be the other boundary of H. Let e: ∂ → ∂ ′ be a homeomorphism preserving the orientation.",
    "The irregular class Θ defines a set A ⊂ ∂ of singular directions.",
    "We define a new surface as Σ:= Σ(Θ):= Σ \\ e(A), that is, for each singular direction d ∈ A, we remove from Σ the corresponding tangential puncture e(d) (see Figure 3).",
    "For each d ∈ A, let us then denote by γ d a small positive loop in Σ starting from d, going around the tangential puncture e(d) (and no other puncture) in a positive sense and going back to d. Definition 3.4."
